  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Histologically or cytologically confirmed metastatic lung cancer or gastrointestinal
             cancer

          -  WHO performance status 0, 1 or 2

          -  Able to walk at least 100 meters independently without crutches or walking frame
             assessed by the treating physician on the basis of the patient's history and physical
             condition

          -  Receiving palliative treatment

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Enteral and/or parenteral nutrition within 1 month previous to study participation

          -  History of ileus within one month

          -  Known brain metastases or symptomatic bone metastases

          -  Psychiatric disorder precluding understanding of information on trial related topics
             and giving informed consent.

          -  Any serious underlying medical condition which could impair the ability of the patient
             to participate in the trial
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
